The paper focuses on evaluating the sim2real predictivity of a simulator for embodied navigation, which is a problem in robotics (cs.RO). The evaluation involves using computer vision techniques to scan a physical lab space and create a virtual replica, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses AI agents learning to cheat in simulators, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a library for seamless execution of code on a simulated agent and a physical robot, which is a contribution to systems and control (cs.SY).
